## About The Project

This is a simple web-based multiple-choice Quiz Game where users can test their knowledge by answering random questions. The game displays one question at a time with clickable answer options. A score is tracked throughout the game, and feedback is shown after each question.

This project aims to demonstrate basic JavaScript interactivity, event handling, and DOM manipulation in a fun and educational format.

<p align="right">(<a href="#readme-top">back to top</a>)</p>

---

## Features

- Multiple-choice question interface
- Real-time score tracking
- Answer validation and feedback
- Next question logic with reset on completion
- Support for basic randomization of question order (optional future feature)

<p align="right">(<a href="#readme-top">back to top</a>)</p>

